What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Coconut Yogurt Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Coconut yogurt is crafted through the fermentation of coconut milk using live cultures, resulting in a lusciously thick texture and a tangy taste. Rich in beneficial healthy saturated fats suc as lauric acid and caprylic acid, it contributes to gut health and offers advantages such as weight management, enhanced digestion, and diminished inflammation. This yogurt is accessible in both conventional and organic options, catering to individuals seeking a dairy-free or vegan substitute for traditional yogurt.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global coconut yogurt market which was USD 101.40 million in 2023, would rocket up to USD 260.17 million by 2031, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 12.50% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. “Conventional” dominates the type segment of the global coconut yogurt market due to increasing consumer preferences for natural and sustainable food choices, aligning with a growing demand for organic and health-conscious products. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

